ChangeLog for DVDRip

1.0
Fri, 28 Mar 2003
  * Minor fixes and improvements
  * libdvdread and libdvdcss updated to 0.9.4 and 1.2.6

0.9
Thu, 13 Feb 2003
  * Back to the libdvdread/libdvdcss method, which is quite more flexible.
  * CLI and GUI mode are available
  * GUI allows to easily rip DVD titles or DVD files
  * Cleaner code, more tests; this release should be pretty more usable/stable than old ones
  * Includes a basic documentation for use with Ffmpeg

0.5
Fri, 31 Jan 2003

  * DVDRip no longer uses directly libdvdcss and libdvdread. All this code has been trashed, now DVDRip is no more than a front-end for the ripping capability of the VideoLAN client 0.5
  * It can send the data on the standard output

0.4
Tue, 12 Nov 2002

  * Now DVDRip automatically changes the libdvdcss method if something goes wrong
  * Minor improvements

0.3
Sat, 9 Nov 2002

  * Added the capability to rip DVD titles into single files
  * Minor fixes and improvements

0.2
Fri, 8 Nov 2002

  * Added a status window
  * Added a separate thread for the rip process

0.1
Tue, 5 Nov 2002

  * First version.
